Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Trim the @carrots{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into
roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Pop them onto a large #baking tray{},
drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.
Add the @British Honey Mustard Sausages{8} to the same tray.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the carrots are tender
and the sausages are browned and cooked through, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages.
> They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Pour the boiling water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife
through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Onion Gravy ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a small #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring often, until softened,
~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @chives{1}(roughly chopped) (use scissors if easier).

Once the onions are soft, lower the heat to medium and add the
@balsamic vinegar{1%tsp}. Cook until sticky, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @water{75%ml} for the sauce to the #onion pan{} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @redcurrant jelly{25%g}. Simmer
until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of
water if it's a little thick.

== Chive Mash ==

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan.

Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @milk{1%splash}(if you have any)
and roughly mash with a #potato masher{}. Stir through the chives and season
to taste with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Share the chive mash between your plates and serve the sausages and carrots
alongside. Spoon the onion gravy over to finish.

Enjoy!